Israel's inflation rate for May was0.6 pct, the lowest since last July when there was no increase,the Central Bureau of Statistics said.    In April, inflation was 2.2 pct and the figure for May lastyear was 1.6 pct. The rate for the first five months of 1987was 7.5 pct, the bureau said.    The annual inflation rate for the past 12 months was 20.3pct, a bureau spokesman said.    Israeli inflation was running at an annual rate of morethan 400 pct until the government imposed an austerity plancontrolling wages and prices in mid-1985. REUTER&#3;